  {
    "slug": "eisenhower-fellowships",
    "title": "Eisenhower Fellowships Impact Report",
    "sourcePath": "/portfolio-collections/my-portfolio/project-title-6",
    "description": "Silver ADDY, American Advertising Federation District 2\n\nEisenhower Fellowships supports dynamic change agents through a transformative fellowship experience and lifelong engagement in a global network. The Impact Report is the 70 year-old organization’s first public, data-driven report on the impact of their programs. The report is based on external impact evaluations and extensive internal surveys of all recent international and USA Fellows.It is an A5, illustrated, 50-page perfect bound book with a spot gloss foil. The design includes friendly spot illustrations and narrative vignettes of select Fellows to break-up the data for approachability. The book, first distributed at an executive meeting on the 130th anniversary of the birth President Dwight D. Eisenhower, was met with enthusiasm from the board of trustees.\n\nKathy Mueller, Art Direction\nRobin Goffman, Senior Designer\nEva Schenck, Illustrator",
